eed appears.\n- Keep the remaining-gap result fixed: with no containment trigger in the current review window, the only unresolved Task 6 work is the live-thread resolver pair plus the syntax-check step that follows the future code change.\n- Keep the next pass hardening-first: execute the remaining Task 6 stale-thread validation work in `task-plans/codex-team-mailbox-loop-task-plan.md` by adding one shared live-thread resolver in `src/host/team-coordination.js`, sourcing it from `panel.lastPayload.dashboard.threads`, and using it only in `assignTaskToThread`, `claimTaskForThread`, `heartbeatThread`, `blockTaskForThread`, and `completeTaskForThread`.\n- Keep the execution boundary fixed: do not expand that slice into mailbox UI changes, stale-lease recovery, or broader supervisor flow changes.\n- Keep the closure rule fixed: the resolver slice should close both Task 6 thread-validation checkboxes together, because the resolver is the concrete implementation of the stale-thread rejection outcome.\n- If the hardening pass finds risk to current stable behavior, pause feature expansion and route the following pass to containment or rollback-friendly isolation.\n\n---LATEST-NOTES---\n--- .claude/plans/loloop/evolution-2026-04-16-mailbox-sole-hardening-target.md ---\n## Loop Type\n\n- type: analysis\n\n## What Changed\n\n- Audited the latest mailbox review window and found no new lifecycle, board/tab, cadence, or task-plan/code regression.\n- Added one explicit sole-hardening-target line in `ACTIVE_PLAN.md` so repeated evidence-free analysis passes keep the Task 6 resolver slice as the only bounded hardening target.\n\n## Plan\n\n- Active plan: `.claude/plans/ACTIVE_PLAN.md`\n- Current milestone: follow-on track — `task-plans/codex-team-mailbox-loop-task-plan.md`\n- Bounded target: preserve the Task 6 resolver slice as the sole bounded hardening target during another analysis-only pass\n\n## Review Window\n\n- reviewed loops: `evolution-2026-04-16-mailbox-stable-next-step